TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hall, Brian J.
AU  - Liebman, Jeffrey B.
T1  - Are CEOs Really Paid Like Bureaucrats?*
PY  - 1998
Y1  - 1998/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355398555702
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 113
IS  - 3
SP  - 653
EP  - 691
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A common view is that there is little correlation between firm performance and CEO pay. Using a new fifteen-year panel data set of CEOs in the largest, publicly traded U. S. companies, we document a strong relationship between firm performance and CEO compensation. This relationship is generated almost entirely by changes in the value of CEO holdings of stock and stock options. In addition, we show that both the level of CEO compensation and the sensitivity of compensation to firm performance have risen dramatically since 1980, largely because of increases in stock option grants.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355398555702
ER  - 



